Description:
A Brand New Take On Modern Coburg Living.
Ray White Projects proudly presents a brand new standard of living with any of these feature-packed town residences in a premier inner-north lifestyle location 8km (approx.) from Melbourne's CBD.
Not only will you save thousands of dollars in stamp duty fees by buying off the plan, but also be the first to sample the extraordinary level of detail, refined finishes, chic decor and luxurious nature of these smartly designed residences, which offer a selection of floorplan options to cater for an array of lifestyle requirements.
While designs may differ between each townhouse, all feature a generous open-plan living domain with a seamless indoor-outdoor design, gourmet kitchen with quality stainless steel appliances, deluxe designer bathrooms with floor-to-ceiling tiling, and off-street parking with ROW access.
Meticulously designed by renowned architectural firm Archsign, a long list of carefully considered features adorn each townhouse, including high square set ceilings throughout, engineered timber flooring, carpeted bedrooms, landscaped gardens (selected residences) and much more.
Secure your place today and look forward to an elite standard of inner-north living within walking distance of Sydney Road shops, bars, cafes and trams, Coburg train station, bus services, Coburg Leisure Centre, City Oval/Bridges Reserve and Coburg Library and minutes from Coburg primary and high schools, Coburg Lake, the Merri Creek Trail and Citylink.
*Disclaimer: the images are for illustrative purposes and whilst every effort is made for accuracy of the image, the development may not be an exact reflection.

Description:
Generosity Of Space And Light
***Strictly private inspections only - Contact Agent***
Nazih Abbouchi is proud to present....
If generosity of space and light are things you're unwilling to sacrifice for low-maintenance living, then this three bedroom two bathroom townhouse will not disappoint. Privately set in a boutique block of four, its house like proportions through an open plan design and inviting alfresco courtyard will appeal to keen entertainers; with its CaesarStone island kitchen featuring 900mm cooking and extensive soft-close cabinetry at the heart of it all. Double bedrooms with robes share two stylish bathrooms, the light-filled master with ensuite. There are hardwood floors, ducted heating/cooling, an alarm, garage with remote and carspace/or courtyard via ROW and with internal access. In a premier position a short walk to Coburg Station, buses, Sydney Road specialty shopping, cafes and more.

Description:
Captivating Californian with Land to Expand!
***Please contact us via email or phone to speak about your options to privately inspect this property. Thank you.***
Immaculately presented and perfectly positioned, this gorgeous period home provides an inner-urban lifestyle immediate quality and Coburg convenience - all on a sizeable allotment with plenty of scope to further enhance and extend in the future (STCA). Beyond the eternally attractive facade, discover a light-filled interior comprising two bedrooms (both with built-in robes), period-inspired central bathroom complete with clawfoot tub and separate (second) WC. Add to this a spacious lounge and adjoining dining room leading through to the contemporary-style kitchen with tiled splashbacks, soft-close cabinetry, dishwasher and oven/gas cooktop. Other stand-out features include high ceilings, solid timber floors, ducted heating and evaporative cooling, solar/gas hot water, plus a full-width decked verandah overlooking the substantial backyard with established gardens and veggie patches, rainwater tank, large storage shed and gated side driveway. A short stroll to Reynard Street buses and Melville Road trams, St Fidelis and Coburg West primary schools, it's also close to popular cafes, Moreland Station, Coburg's renowned retail precinct as well as easy access to Citylink.
32m x 12.19m = 390sqm approx.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending a Private Appointment, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from our team and refrain from touching any items/fixtures and doors within the property. You must wear a face mask and we will provide gloves for your appointment. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Alluring Californian Offers Modern Living - Virtual Tours Available! Contact Agent To Arrange!
With the health and well-being of our community being front of mind we have additional measures in place at all property inspections. Our COVID-19 conditions of entry are available for your viewing click here: https://bit.ly/347XJd6
Charmingly positioned in Coburg West's family-friendly neighbourhood, this dazzling three bedroom, two bathroom Californian Bungalow holds original character whilst providing contemporary style and comfort. Period inspired; high decorative ceilings, solid timber floors and sunny leadlight bay windows flow throughout the property, as the spacious lounge boasts a timber mantle fire place and progresses to an open sunroom/study alcove. Crafted for home chefs, the sundrenched stone kitchen/meals is well-equipped in modern Miele and Neff appliances, lengthy breakfast bar and ample soft closing cabinetry, before beautiful glass doors present an undercover entertaining area and landscaped backyard. Serviced by two separate bathrooms, the generous bedrooms offer privacy and are fitted with conveniently large built-in-robes. Further luxuries include laundry with great storage, ducted gas heating, refrigerated cooling, solar panels and lockup garage with rear laneway access. A short stroll to St Fidelis and Coburg West primary schools, Shore Reserve and Melville Road trams, Strathmore to East Coburg bus plus bus transport on Bell St and Moreland Road, while also close to Coburg Station, Sydney Road's shopping precinct and CityLink.

Description:
Great Design Where Elegance & Functionality Meet!
In one of Melbourne's most desired suburbs this distinctive, stylish home is sure to impress either the owner occupier or astute investor alike. Finished to a superior level of quality and immaculately presented, this home has been respectfully enhanced to boast a fresh, functional and naturally lit open plan layout lending itself entirely to a comfortable and modern lifestyle.
This beautiful home features high ceilings throughout, downstairs includes a guest master bedroom with a walk-in wardrobe and your own semi-private ensuite. A light filled open plan dining/living area with European Oak timber flooring and adjoining onto the stunning kitchen. The kitchen itself features 900mm Bosch appliances including a dishwasher, double sink under mount sink with Pendent lighting, double pantry, soft closing cabinetry, 40mm Calcutta stone bench tops with a waterfall finish and complemented by the tiled splash back. Leading out through the large sliding doors and onto your own private Merbau decking area, overlooking the double garage and the landscaped rear yard perfect for entertaining family and friends.
Heading upstairs via the Victorian Ash hardwood staircase you will find three generous size bedrooms all with built in wardrobes and serviced by the immaculate shared central bathroom with floor to ceiling tiles. While the master bedroom has its own ensuite with bathtub and shower.
Additionally, this family home includes a separate fully functional laundry, Bosch alarm system, Tech intercom system, blue stone tiled front porch and matte black fixtures throughout. Within walking distance to public transport, local schools, Upfield Bike path, the vibrant Sydney, Moreland and Melville Road with its cafes and restaurants on offer, ensuring that nothing is ever out of reach!

Description:
Expansive Dimensions, Endless Potential
Located directly across from Merri Creek on a spectacular block size of approximately 918m2, this well-loved four bedroom, two bathroom home promises exciting possibilities to rebuild or redevelop (subject to council approval). Spacious dimensions enhance the formal lounge, separate dinning and retro kitchen comprising gas cooking appliances, while a vast yard backs onto Duggan Reserve and boasts veggie gardens with a rear accessible garden shed/workshop. Serviced by a central bathroom and separate toilet, the large bedrooms (master with built-in-robe) also have access to a second shower. Including ducted heating, laundry, shutter blinds, lockup double garage/hidden cellar and off-street-parking. Surrounded by scenic parkland, it's moments to Nicholson Street, Sydney Road, public transport, various schools and local eateries offering multicultural cuisine.

Embrace a brilliant urban lifestyle and boutique class

Split-system air conditioners, polished floorboards, alarm, powder room, European laundry and secure car space. Mere metres from shops, cafes, schools, two tram lines and Moreland station.

Description:
Industry Excellence!
Due to Melbourne's Stage 4 Restrictions, all Nelson Alexander team members are working from home. Please contact us via email or phone to speak about your options to view this property virtually. Thank you.
An inspired warehouse conversion, prominently displaying all the architectural elements of its industrial past, this two-level townhouse presents an exceptional inner-urban lifestyle/investment opportunity with its generous design, contemporary style and exclusive Pentridge precinct location. A haven of quality and privacy, the home's warm and inviting interior boasts two bedrooms (extra-large master) both with built-in robes and high vaulted ceilings, together with a stylish central bathroom and full-size laundry/second WC. Add to this a versatile open-plan living/meals area accompanied by a well-appointed kitchen complete with stone benchtops, tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and integrated Fisher & Paykel dish drawer. Exposed brickwork, ironwork and timber beams further enhance the ambience of this unique warehouse townhouse, along with solid hardwood floors and split-system heating/cooling (both levels). Step outside to discover a sunny yet wonderfully private rear courtyard which backs onto one of Pentridge's defining bluestone walls, plus the added appeal of a secure entry foyer and undercover parking space. Walking distance to the open spaces of Coburg Lake Reserve and endless Merri Creek trails, it's also close to local schools and childcare services, along with Sydney Road trams, cafes, Coburg Station and renowned shopping precinct.

Description:
Luxurious Family Living
Meticulously renovated with an eye for style and excellence in quality and craftsmanship, upgrade to a higher standard of living with this bright and stylish family home.
Enhanced with contemporary finishes and featuring generous living spaces, relaxed outdoor entertaining and the flexibility of four bedrooms and three living zones, it's a home that delivers the space and style your growing family craves on a glorious 667sqm (approx.) fully landscaped garden allotment.
Being on the elevated side of the road and with a high fence and large front garden, this property provides a superior level of privacy and outlook. The essence of peace and tranquillity extends to the park-like backyard featuring beautiful established gardens, a manicured lawn for children to play, an undercover alfresco for year-round entertaining and a large open-air setting ideal for star-gazing around a fire pit.
Back inside, stretch out and relax in the welcoming living area set against a soothing leafy outlook, and feel inspired with your sleek gourmet kitchen, which boasts commercial grade Neil Perry appliances (Italian made oven, stovetop, rangehood, rotisserie), ASKO stainless steel dishwasher, stone surfaces, plenty of soft close storage space and a large Velux skylight for an endless stream of natural light.
For the ultimate wow factor, a spectacular family bathroom is every bit the celebration of modern design, instantly impressing with its chic bluestone tiling, floating timber vanity, on-trend black tapware, frameless walk-in shower and extra large Victoria + Albert volcanic limestone freestanding bath as its stylish centrepiece.
A bright rear rumpus room can function as a games retreat for the kids, while flexibility is an asset with the large fourth bedroom. Boasting its own bathroom, laundry and private entry, it can accommodate the privacy-craving teenager or extended family members or be converted into a large home office for the working parent.
A further three bedrooms are of generous proportions (all newly carpeted), while a large basement cellar, single garage, additional off-street car space with new 2m high automatic sliding gate, evaporative cooling, ducted heating and polished timber floorboards add another layer of positive appeal.
Enriching your living experience is the family-oriented location, which is within short walking distance of Coburg Hill Shopping Centre, the Merri Creek Trail, transport, Coburg High School, Preston Market, Coburg Lake, swimming pool, Coburg drive in, Sydney Road shops as well as moments from Pentridge Shopping Precinct which will include shopping, dining, a cinema and much more.

Stunning from first glance, this gorgeous three bedroom property flaunts exceptional design, quality fixtures and finishes and inspiring natural light throughout. Unique and evoking more than a little Hamptons style flavour, it features a kitchen, starring timber countertops and 90cm Bosch appliances, adjoining an enticing living/dining area leading to a covered north-facing balcony that is perfect for entertaining friends and family. Bedrooms host tall mirrored built-in robes, one boasts a box bay window with window seat and there's a study nook with fixed desk, plus an elegant fully tiled bathroom with frameless glass shower and powder room. Description:
Distinguished by Quality
Brilliantly conceived and meticulously crafted, the eye-catching renovation and extension of this character-filled, 5 bedroom, Californian Bungalow has created an al fresco entertainers' dream home with an uncompromising commitment to excellence. The home beautifully blends its original charm with high-ceilings, original leadlight windows, restored brickwork archway and original timber doors with a more contemporary, open-plan and al fresco personality, making it perfect for discerning urban families of today.
At its heart, the open-plan kitchen / meals / living is a visually striking space that is suited for gourmet cooking with volumes gleaming 2 pac cabinetry. A full suite of Miele appliances includes an induction cooktop, pyrolytic oven, combination steam oven, warming drawer, range-hood and integrated dishwasher to complement a Fisher & Paykel integrated refrigerator and freezer, whilst a Butler's Pantry is a rare indulgence in which a Vintec wine cabinet and beverage centre is a delight. Seamlessly, the open-plan accommodates all your al fresco aspirations as it opens through glass sliding doors to an undercover deck. This is the perfect setting to gather with friends and family.
Parents will relish the luxury of a fully-tiled 5-star ensuite in which a black-butt timber vanity is appointed with twin basins and where under-floor heating is a welcome friend in the winter months. Impressive birch-ply walk-in robes are not only aesthetically pleasing, but also wonderfully functional, while 3 of the remaining bedrooms are appointed with substantial 2 pac cabinetry built-in robes.
Meanwhile, families will value the flexibility offered by a separate, traditional lounge room that is arranged around its gas-converted open fire place.
With a rare attention to detail, this 6-star energy efficient residence has been impressively finished with blackbutt timber flooring throughout, fully-tiled family bathroom, a powder room and a full-sized laundry, as well as zoned and central ducted heating and refrigerated cooling for year-round comfort, security cameras, secure driveway parking, plantation shutters and 6.6KW solar panels.
Zoned within Strathmore Secondary College, just wander down to Melville Road for a taste of café culture, some strip shopping and city-bound trams, whilst the Upfield bike path and Coburg Leisure Centre are also nearby and Citylink can be accessed in just a few minutes from this terrific inner-northern setting.

Come home to your own sanctuary of a little yesteryear and a lot of modern convenience. This single fronted period home ticks all the boxes in the heart of Coburg, with separate traditional living spaces and features yet modern comforts we all love, you cannot go wrong with this whole package! Not only can you entertain your family and friends indoors but wait until you step outside… A covered and private alfresco decked area with an established leafy garden, an oasis in your backyard. A corner home, ideal for first home buyers, investors and downsizers PLUS near shops, cafés, schools, markets, and public transport. Contact the team today!

- Weatherboard Corner Renovated Victorian House. Built in 1900 approx.
- Land size 236m2 approx. Building size of 11sq approx.
- KITCHEN: Laminate cabinetry with 40mm premium laminate benchtops and breakfast bench. 600mm S/S appliances including dishwasher and double S/S kitchen sink. Pantry and cupboards, finish with timber floorboards
- MEALS: Open plan area with timber floorboards
- LIVING: Separate formal area with timber floorboards and fireplace
- DINING/OFFICE/2nd LIVING: Separate formal dining room OR Home office/study area OR 2nd living area with timber floorboards

*Due to Melbourne's Stage 4 Restrictions, all Nelson Alexander team members are working from home. Please contact us via email or phone to speak about your options to view this property virtually. Thank you. *
Retaining the distinctive character and allure of its industrial origins, this converted warehouse delivers a uniquely stylish and secluded inner-urban lifestyle with its impressive dimensions, quality inclusions and reassuringly secure surrounds. High ceilings across both levels, the home's serene interior comprises two upstairs bedrooms (large master with WIR and sunny balcony) accompanied by a stylish two-way bathroom with frameless shower and floor-to-ceiling tiles, as well as a downstairs guest powder room (second WC). Adding to its appeal is the open-plan living/dining area that's both spacious and versatile complemented by a well-appointed kitchen complete with Ariston appliances (dishwasher, oven and gas cooktop). Other stand-out features of this cool conversion include split-system heating and cooling, additional ceiling fans (dining area and both bedrooms), plus intercom/secure entry and undercover parking space. Completing the picture is a fully-decked private rear courtyard which backs onto one of Pentridge's signature bluestone walls. A short stroll to the open spaces of Coburg Lake Reserve and endless trails along leafy Merri Creek, it's also close to local schools and childcare services, along with Sydney Road trams, cafes, Coburg Station and renowned shopping precinct.

Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you

Description:
**NEW TIME FOR VIRTUAL AUCTION Wednesday 12 August 5.30pm**
Please register your interest in this property so that we can ensure you are included in the Virtual Auction and/or contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior to the Virtual Auction Wednesday 12 August at 5.30pm.
**Due to Melbourne's Stage 4 Restrictions, all Nelson Alexander team members are working from home. Please contact us via email or phone to speak about your options to view this property virtually. Thank you.**
Set upon 755.29m2 (approx.) in a neighbourly tree-lined street & in the same ownership for almost 50 years, this much-loved California Bungalow presents a superb opportunity to establish a new family living environment. Echoing period charm, this delightful property offers immaculate light filled interiors, easycare gardens and potential to add your personal touch and/or extend some time in the future (STCA). It is ideally placed steps to Nicholson Street trams and strolling distance to Sydney Road shops and cafes, Merri Creek parklands and a selection of quality schools. Past the gracious façade and wide foyer is an elegant dining room (possible 4th bedroom) with bay window flowing through double glass doors to a spacious living room with a gas heater, both featuring ornate ceilings. Nearby is a large timber kitchen with gas cooking and family meals area. There are 3 bedrooms, pristine bathroom with a separate w/c and bidet. Step outdoors to a huge sun soaked backyard with a veggie garden, fruit trees and great scope for alfresco entertaining. There is also a side drive that leads to a large garage & workshop with an attached bedroom/studio. Additional features include a separate laundry, separate side entrance off the driveway, a cellar, split system a/c, leadlight windows and gas hot water. A true classic with a bright future! Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd.

Description:
A Palatial Inner-Suburban Pad
* Register to attend an open for inspection*
In order to maintain a maximum of 20 attendees to all Open Inspections, we ask that you please register to attend. By registering your details, you avoid disappointment if more than 20 people attend the inspection and will assist us in keeping the inspections as safe as possible for our team and our clients.
Few studios beguile like this newly renovated two-bedroom ground floor Coburg apartment.
Beautifully positioned in a private street at the heart of Pentridge Village and its historic legacy, the apartments unique floor plan, meticulous design flourishes and fantastic inner-city location make this up-and-coming cultural hotspot an exceptional scoop for professional singles, couples and investors alike.
For starters, the residence is full of thoughtful touches. Think carpeted bedrooms with built-in robes and grandiose windows; laminate timber flooring in the living areas; sparkling stone benchtops and extensive gleaming white cabinetry forming the immaculate kitchen; and a quiet study nook, on the opposite side to the bedrooms to ensure work and rest are separate.
But its the soaring high ceilings and immense panoramic windows that truly set the scene. Bringing the outdoors indoors and bathing its interiors in waves of natural light, each instantly transforms what couldve been a standard run-of-the-mill apartment into a striking and palatial pad that surprises and delights.
Topping it all off is the apartments exquisite location. Just moments from Coburg Farmers Market, Pentridge Cellars and the Glass Den cafe, and within walking distance of the Merri Creek parklands, Coburg Lake, public transport and Sydney Roads array of shops, cafes and restaurants, your every want or whim is within easy reach.
